<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-07-20T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-07-20T16:00:00-05:00" n="501" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d501">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">815.00/2378: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Morales</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-07-20T15:00:00-06:00"><hi rend="italic">July 20,
                                        1922—3 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received July 21—10:10
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>57. Referring to the Department’s telegram of July 19, 7 p.m.<note n="17" xml:id="d501fn17"><hi rend="italic">Supra.</hi></note> The President
                            is very grateful to the Department for the prompt action taken with the
                            Nicaraguan Government. Diplomatic relations will not be severed without
                            first advising the Department. This Government has situation completely
                            under control. No further trouble contemplated and I have kept Legation
                            at Managua fully advised by telegram.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Morales</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>